{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Dynamic dashboard for launching sessions and recent projects.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 ========================================= \u55357 ?\u57041 ? AUTO-BOOT SETUP INSTRUCTIONS \u55357 ?\u57041 ?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To make this dashboard open automatically when Reaper starts:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open the Actions List in Reaper (shortcut: ?).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for "TLC Dashboard".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Right-click on it and select "Copy selected action command ID".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab In the top menu, go to: Extensions > SWS Options > Enable global startup action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Paste the ID and hit OK!\sa180\par}
}
